<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
 *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Providian Financial, up 8 11/16 at 92    	
</P>
<P>
	Several investment firms upgraded their ratings on Providian, a  
credit-card issuer, after the company reaffirmed its earnings 
outlook for 1999 and 2000. Providian also said officials are 
cooperating with authorities investigating alleged deceptive 
business practices. 

</P>
<P>
 *DLJ Direct, up 9 15/16 at 39 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The online brokerage run by Donaldson, Lufkin &AMP; Jenrette  
continued to gain in its second day of trading. DLJ Direct, which 
was priced at 20, closed at 30 Wednesday, a respectable gain but 
not close to the spectacular launch of earlier Internet-related 
offerings. 

</P>
<P>
 *Texaco Inc., down 2 3/8 at 62 7/8  
</P>
<P>
 *Chevron Corp., down 1 7/8 at 92 3/16 
</P>
<P>
	The Wall Street Journal reported that merger talks between  
Texaco and Chevron have stalled. Speculation about a $42 billion 
deal has rumbled through the market since earlier this month. 

</P>
<P>
 *Pfizer Inc., up 3 7/16 at 104 7/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Pfizer named Henry McKinnell president and chief operating  
officer. McKinnell, president of Pfizer Pharmaceuticals Group, is 
seen as a likely successor to chairman and chief executive officer 
William Steere Jr. when he retires in June 2001. 

</P>
<P>
 *Capital Re, down 3 1/4 at 16  
</P>
<P>
 *ACE Ltd., down 1 3/16 at 30 5/16 
</P>
<P>
	Bermuda-based insurer ACE Ltd. will buy reinsurer Capital Re  
Corp. in a stock swap valued at about $610 million. 

</P>
<P>
 *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *StarMedia Network, up 11 9/16 at 37 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Latin American online network Wednesday began trading on  
Nasdaq. StarMedia runs the most popular ``portal'' or gateway to 
the World Wide Web for Spanish-speaking users in Latin America. 

</P>
<P>
 *Marcam Solutions, up 3 7/16 at 7 3/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Invensys PLC will acquire Marcam for $7.50 a share in cash, or  
about $60 million. Marcam makes software for business planning. 

</P>
<P>
 *Autobytel.com Inc., up 5 5/16 at 21 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The company said in a news release that it does $24 million in  
car sales each day. Autobytel.com operates an automotive Web site 
and provides a network of dealers with access to online car buyers. 


</P>
</TEXT>
