<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NASA Honors Memory of CNN Reporter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. (AP) -- In a launch-day salute to John  
Holliman, NASA today named its press auditorium after the late CNN 
correspondent. 
</P>
<P>
	Holliman, who covered the space program and even haggled with  
the Russians for a ride on Mir, was killed in a car accident 
outside Atlanta in September. 
</P>
<P>
	``John was a true space fan,'' said NASA Administrator Daniel  
Goldin. ``And he conveyed that sense of excitement to his audience. 
John didn't simply report on space issues. He conveyed the deep 
passion he had for his stories.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The dedication followed Discovery's liftoff on a space station  
mission. 
</P>
<P>
	``We all know John has the best seat in the house, and if he  
were here, he would be the first to tell the world about the 
successful liftoff this morning,'' Goldin said. 
</P>
<P>
	Holliman's widow, Dianne, and 5-year-old son, Jay, attended the  
ceremony at the Kennedy Space Center press site, as did Tom 
Johnson, chairman of the CNN News Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
