<HEADLINE> Two Die in Cleveland Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- A man killed his cousin at a metals plant  
Thursday, shot the plant owner when he tried to intervene, then 
killed himself. 
</P>
<P>
	The gunman arrived on his day off at Buffex Metal Finishing and  
while fighting with his cousin, pulled a gun and shot him, police 
said. Authorities have not released the names of the cousins. 
</P>
<P>
	The plant's owner, Orlando Ray Quintana, 33, was shot in the  
chest when he tried to break up the fight, police said. He was in 
guarded condition Thursday at a hospital. 
</P>
