<HEADLINE> Kenyan, Bosnian Envoy Nominated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	YULEE, Fla. (AP) -- President Clinton on Thursday nominated  
Johnnie Carson to be ambassador to Kenya and Thomas J. Miller as 
ambassador to Bosnia. 
</P>
<P>
	Carson, of Chicago, is deputy assistant secretary of state for  
African affairs. He was ambassador to Zimbabwe from 1995-97 and 
Uganda from 1991-94, and was a Peace Corps volunteer in Tanzania in 
the 1960s. 
</P>
