<HEADLINE> Ackroyd and Dad Give Millenium Gift </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Dan Aykroyd and his father, Peter, have joined  
the rush to mark the millennium. 
</P>
<P>
	On Wednesday, the pair launched the ``Our Millennium'' project,  
which invites Canadians to give millennium gifts to their 
communities -- and give people something more than a good party to 
remember the dawn of the next 1,000 years. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think you have to look in your community where there's a  
need for something,'' said Dan Ackroyd, an Ontario native and a 
star of such films as ``Ghostbusters'' and ``The Blues Brothers.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Aykroyd family made the first donation with the gift of a  
Braille keyboard to a Kingston-area office of the Canadian National 
Institute for the Blind. The keyboard allows sightless people to 
translate the written word from the Internet. 
</P>
<P>
	The Aykroyds are promoting such ideas as shopping clubs for  
seniors, playgrounds and the planting of flowers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Canada Millennium Partnership Program is a federal  
initiative that helps fund community projects to celebrate the next 
1,000 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
