<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tips To Avoid Stolen Baggage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Travel agents and airport police officers have several  
suggestions about how to keep from getting your bags stolen at an 
airport baggage claim area: 

</P>
<P>
	--''About the only way to ensure it's safe is being close to the  
exit portal and watching for it and taking it off the belt as soon 
as possible,'' said Chief Tom Shehan of the Dallas-Fort Worth 
Airport police. In 1998, his officers arrested a man who stole an 
estimated 500 bags from DFW baggage belts and sold the contents at 
a flea market. 
</P>
<P>
	--Keep your bags with you until you leave the airport.  
</P>
<P>
	--When using a telephone, do not leave computers, carry-on bags  
or wallets unattended -- even for a moment. 
</P>
<P>
	--In the event a bag is taken by mistake, it helps to have your  
name both on the outside and the inside, said the American Society 
of Travel Agents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
