<HEADLINE> Rapids 4, Clash 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Wolde Harris and Jorge Dely Valdes had a goal and  
an assist each to lead the Colorado Rapids to a 4-2 victory over 
the San Jose Clash on Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The win marks the seventh consecutive victory for the Rapids,  
and moves them into second place in the Western Conference, one 
point behind Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
	Ronald Cerritos earned a goal for San Jose less than a minute  
into the game. But the Rapids came back with Harris converting a 
penalty kick at 20 minutes to even the score. 
</P>
