disaster aid will begin to see checks next week, Agriculture 
Secretary Dan Glickman said today. Glickman told a Senate 
Agriculture hearing that payments to about 260,000 farmers will 
begin on Tuesday. The government already distributed $2.8 billion 
in payments to compensate for low prices, but distributing the $2.3 
billion in disaster payments, which cover disasters and disease, 
was burdensome, officials said. 

</P>
