<HEADLINE> GOP Celebrates Welfare Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Rep. Bill Archer, a top House Republican,  
still remembers being called names when he pushed the 1996 welfare 
overhaul, so he's feeling more than a little vindicated by the good 
news so far. 
</P>
<P>
	``Where are the children starving on the sewer grates?'' he  
asked Thursday. 
</P>
