<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-27 11:01:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Virenque Wins Tour of Italy Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RAPALLO, Italy (AP) -- Richard Virenque beat Santiago Blanco in a  
two-way sprint Thursday to capture the 13th stage of the Tour of 
Italy -- his first win in a year. 
</P>
<P>
	The French cyclist, at the center of last year's Tour of France  
doping scandal, outsprinted the Spaniard at the finish line in this 
Italian riviera resort following a long-lasting breakaway. 
</P>
<P>
	Virenque raised his arms in triumph as he crossed the finish  
line and shouted his joy for a long-waited victory following months 
of doping allegations. 
</P>
<P>
	Another Frenchman, national champion Laurent Jalabert, retained  
the pink jersey of overall leader as he finished in the main group 
34 seconds behind the winner. 
</P>
<P>
	Jalabert, who clinched the race leadership last Sunday, held a  
four-seconds lead over defending Giro champion Marco Pantani. 
</P>
<P>
	Virenque completed the spill-marred 150.6-mile distance from  
Sassuolo to Rapallo in 6 hours, 55 minutes, 34 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
	Cyclists will rest Friday in the only day-off of the 22-stage  
Italian cycling marathon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
