<HEADLINE> Worker Trapped in Plane's Cargo Bin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- A Delta Air Lines flight turned around shortly  
after takeoff Thursday after a baggage handler was discovered 
accidentally locked in the cargo bin. 
</P>
<P>
	The Atlanta-bound flight returned to Cleveland Hopkins  
International Airport shortly after its 5:27 a.m. takeoff when a 
flight attendant heard banging from inside the bin. 
</P>
