	``At this point, we're not sure how he got in there,'' said  
airline spokesman Todd Clay. ``He appeared to be shaken up, but he 
was not injured in any way.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Emergency workers met the plane as it landed and examined the  
worker, who was not identified. The cargo bin is pressurized and 
heated. 
</P>
<P>
	The flight left for Atlanta about an hour later.  



</P>
