<HEADLINE> Fox Launching Health TV Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Fox Entertainment Group Inc. will launch The  
Health Network in mid-July. 
</P>
<P>
	The Health Network will launch on cable and the Internet with 17  
million cable and satellite subscribers in all 50 states, Fox said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Health Network is a new media company that will provide  
health information to consumers, physicians and hospitals through a 
cable television and the Internet. 
</P>
<P>
	The network is a joint venture between Fox Liberty Ventures and  
AHN Ltd. Partners, which was created by the merger of AHN's 
cable-TV network, America's Health Network; its Web site, AHN.com; 
and Fox's fit tv earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
	AHN is controlled by health-care industry entrepreneurs Rick  
Scott and David Vandewater. Scott was chief executive officer of 
Columbia/HCA Healthcare Corp, the nation's biggest hospital chain, 
until he quit amid a federal Medicare fraud investigation in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox Entertainment Group develops and produces worldwide  
distribution of feature films and television programs, television 
broadcasting and cable network programming. 


</P>
