<HEADLINE> French Favorite Mauresmo Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- One day after her loss to Martina Hingis, Amelie  
Mauresmo left the French Open in a wheelchair on Thursday after 
spraining her left ankle while playing doubles with Julie Halard 
Decugis. 
</P>
<P>
	The match against Jana Novotna and Natasha Zvereva had been tied  
at 4-4 in the first set. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *STRANGE GIFT:* Ball boys and girls at Roland Garros got a  
surprise Thursday when a player left them underwear. 
</P>
<P>
	After her match against Ai Sugiyama, Italian Silvia Farina gave  
away some clothing to the ball boys and girls. 
</P>
<P>
	When the ball boys opened the package they found not only a  
T-shirt and some shorts but also panties and a bra. They brought 
the underwear to the lost and found. The other clothing was kept 
and will be given away to ball boys and girls in a lottery at the 
end of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *SAY YES TO DRUG TESTING:* Steffi Graf spoke out in favor of  
more rigorous drug testing at the French Open. Graf is also in 
favor of testing during the off-season. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think (drug testing) is something that needs to be done a  
lot stricter,'' she said. ``The other thing is, so far I've only 
heard of drug testing during tournaments, and I've never heard of 
it off tournaments or during training season.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Graf said she felt that the women's tour should follow the lead  
of Olympic sports that have off-season drug testing. 
</P>
<P>
	At the 1993 French Open, Graf told reporters that she hadn't  
been tested for drugs on the tour for eight years. On Thursday, she 
said that had changed. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's maybe two or three times a year now,'' Graf said.  
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *SOUND ADVICE:* During her match against the No. 2-seeded  
Lindsay Davenport, 16-year-old Justine Henin got some good tips 
from the supportive French audience. 
</P>
<P>
	``Make her run !'' spectators rooting for the Belgian shouted.  
</P>
<P>
	Henin said afterwards that she should have listened. ``It was  
probably good advice,'' she said. ``I should have made her run 
more.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Henin lost in three sets to Davenport in three sets, who was  
quick to praise her opponent. 
</P>
<P>
	``Anyone that can play that type of game definitely has a great  
future,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
                             	------	 
</P>
<P>
	 *WILLIAMS RELAX:* The Williams sisters took advantage of the  
lovely weather in Paris to enjoy an early sunbath with some ball 
boys Thursday morning. 
</P>
<P>
	When Venus and Serena passed by the Suzanne Lenglen court, they  
saw some ball boys resting on the grass. The sisters decided to 
take a little break and join them. The ball boys were very taken 
with the friendly attitude of the sisters. 


</P>
