<HEADLINE> Cardigans Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 3,800 Tommy Hilfiger infant cardigans  
are being recalled after a plastic snap on a cardigan snapped, 
presenting a choking hazard to the infant. 
</P>
<P>
	Hilfiger received one report of a snap detaching from the front  
of the fleece cardigan, but the baby wasn't injured, the U.S. 
Consumer Product Safety Commission said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The recalled cardigans range in size from 3 to 24 months, and  
were sold at high-end department stores nationwide from August 
through October 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The commission advises consumers to stop using the cardigans  
immediately, and call the manufacturer at 877-TOMMYCARES to arrange 
for an exchange or refund. 

</P>
</TEXT>
