<HEADLINE> BMW Recalls New 3-Series Sedans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MUNICH, Germany (AP) -- Luxury automaker BMW announced a recall  
Thursday of all cars from its newly redesigned 3-series of small 
sedans because of technical problems with side airbags and brakes. 
</P>
<P>
	BMW said the side airbag could accidentally inflate in some  
circumstances, such as when the car brushes against a curb. In 
addition, some cars could experience brake failure if an improperly 
installed safety clip becomes loose, it said. 
</P>
<P>
	Owners of 3-series cars, introduced in April 1998, should bring  
the car to their dealer to have it checked, BMW said. 
</P>
