<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Prosecution Rests in Police Torture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Prosecutors in a federal police brutality trial  
ended their case Thursday by showing the jury the whisk half of a 
broken broomstick -- the other half of which, they said, was used to 
torture a Haitian immigrant. 
</P>
<P>
	The closing came the same week that one of the defendants  
dropped out of the trial after pleading guilty to the attack, a 
move that the jury was informed of by the trial judge, who denied 
motions to declare a mistrial for the remaining defendants. 
</P>
<P>
	In final prosecution testimony on Thursday, Lt. Vincent DiDonato  
said the broken broom was found during a search of the stationhouse 
six days after Abner Louima was sodomized in the bathroom. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators never recovered the stick used in the attack,  
which shocked the city for its alleged brutality and has strained 
police relations with minorities. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutor Alan Vinegrad walked in front of the jury box holding  
up the broken broom before announcing that the prosecution was 
resting after a month of testimony by 50 witnesses and a dramatic 
guilty plea by the lead defendant. 
</P>
<P>
	Outside court, defense attorney Stephen Worth described the  
finale as ``a prosecutorial cheap shot.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a technique called waving the bloody shirt,'' he said.  
``There absolutely no proof that this is the other half of the 
notorious stick.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Earlier this week, Officer Justin Volpe shook the trial by  
pleading guilty to civil rights charges. He could be sentenced to 
life in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Volpe, 27, admitted ramming a stick into a handcuffed Louima's  
rectum, pulling it out and putting it up to his face to humiliate 
him. He said he mistakenly believed the prisoner had punched him 
when police tried to quell a disturbance outside a nightclub in 
1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Charles Schwarz faces the most serious charge among the  
remaining four defendants -- that he held Louima, 32, down in the 
bathroom assault. 
</P>
<P>
	Schwarz and Officers Thomas Wiese and Thomas Bruder also are  
charged with beating Louima in a patrol car en route to the police 
precinct. Sgt. Michael Bellomo, their supervisor, is charged with 
covering up the incident. 
</P>
<P>
	The trial resumes Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
