<HEADLINE> MLB, SportsLine Team Up for Web Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Major League Baseball and SportsLine USA Inc.  
are teaming up to provide an enhanced Web site that includes live 
audio broadcasts and real-time coverage of every game in an 
animated format. 
</P>
<P>
	The multi-year exclusive agreement also covers SportsLine's  
production of Web sites for the All-Star Game and the World Series, 
according to a joint statement issued Wednesday. The Fort 
Lauderdale, Fla.-based SportsLine produced the sites for those 
events last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Up until now, Major League Baseball has produced  
majorleaguebaseball.com on its own. 
</P>
<P>
	The enhanced sites will include daily and historical video  
highlights, real-time statistics and updates, team and player 
information, sale of official licensed merchandise, fantasy 
competitions and interactive online games. SportsLine's Baseball 
Live provides pitch-by-pitch coverage of games in animation. 
</P>
<P>
	Baseball's site will be re-launched in June with the added  
features. 
</P>
<P>
	SportsLine, which produces CBS SportsLine, also serves as the  
primary sports content provider for America Online Inc., Netscape 
Communications Corp. and Excite Inc. 

</P>
</TEXT>
