<HEADLINE> Mets' Isringhausen Strains Elbow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- New York Mets pitcher Jason Isringhausen may  
miss his next pitching turn because of a mild tendon strain in his 
right elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	Isringhausen was diagnosed Thursday by Dr. David Altchek, the  
team physician, after he experienced discomfort in the elbow 
following his start at Pittsburgh on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Altchek performed reconstructive surgery on the elbow Jan. 13,  
1998, two years after the pitcher had arthroscopic shoulder and 
elbow surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	Isringhausen began the season with the Mets' Norfolk farm club  
and was recalled for the start Monday night when New York placed 
Bobby Jones on the disabled list. He was to make his second start 
Saturday against Arizona but now is listed as day-to-day. 
</P>
