<HEADLINE> Student Lands Date With TLC's Lopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Nothing ventured, nothing gained -- Malcolm  
Blair landed a dream date for prom with a simple letter to a 
musical star. 
</P>
<P>
	The Strawberry Mansion High School student sent Lisa ``Left  
Eye'' Lopes of the Grammy-winning trio TLC a letter and asked her 
to be his date for prom. Lopes accepted the invitation with a 
personal phone call. 
</P>
<P>
	The two entered the prom Saturday dressed in white  
reptile-print, vinyl-like outfits provided by Lopes, who had them 
made by Philadelphia fashion designer Kyle Young. 
</P>
<P>
	Malcolm said the date was his dream come true.  
</P>
<P>
	``I thought she was going to be, like, stuck-up or something  
like that, even though that's not the way she seems on TV,'' 
Malcolm said. ``I didn't expect her to be down-to-earth.'' 
</P>
<P>
	TLC recently released its third album, ``Fanmail,'' and it has  
sold over one million copies. Their latest hit is the song ``No 
Scrubs.'' 
</P>
