<HEADLINE> Colts Lineman Nabbed on Gun Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WESTFIELD, Ind. (AP) -- Police charged Indianapolis Colts  
defensive tackle Larry Chester early Thursday with carrying a 
handgun without a license after a traffic stop. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Michael V. Richards stopped Chester, 23, about 1:30 a.m.  
for speeding and noticed the handgun in the glove compartment of 
Chester's car, according to a police report. 
</P>
<P>
	It is illegal to carry a handgun in a vehicle without a license.  
</P>
<P>
	Chester was not ticketed for speeding. He was booked in the  
Hamilton County Jail on the gun charge and freed on $2,500 bond. 
</P>
