<HEADLINE> Gov. Regales Fans With Bawdy Tales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	YORBA LINDA, Calif. (AP) -- Now it's Jesse ``The Bawdy'' Ventura.  
</P>
<P>
	The governor of Minnesota regaled admirers Thursday at the  
Richard Nixon Library &AMP; Birthplace with the off-color stories of 
his Navy years and detailed his rise from professional wrestler to 
politician. 
</P>
<P>
	Promoting his book, ``I Ain't Got Time to Bleed: Reworking the  
Body Politic from the Bottom Up,'' Ventura had no apologies for its 
bluntness and instead invoked Jack Nicholson's ``You can't handle 
the truth'' speech from the movie ``A Few Good Men.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Most people can't handle it because sometimes the truth  
hurts,'' Ventura told an audience of 600 that included senior 
citizens, fellow Reform Party members and youths who overflowed the 
library auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
	The governor was referring to parts of the book detailing his  
visit to a Nevada brothel when he was a Navy SEAL -- passages 
criticized as a bad example for young people. 
</P>
<P>
	``I better not do this because 25 years from now I might be a  
role model? The thought never entered this thick Slovak head,'' 
Ventura said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
