<HEADLINE> Lakers Refuse Comment on Rambis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- The Los Angeles Lakers will not discuss  
a report the team is leaning heavily toward hiring Kurt Rambis as 
permanent coach. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's no comment,'' Lakers spokesman John Black said today  
when asked about a Los Angeles Times report quoting several 
unidentified sources say key Laker executives favor the selection 
of Rambis. 
</P>
<P>
	Rambis took over on an interim basis from Del Harris in February  
and, despite the Dennis Rodman fiasco, he led the Lakers past 
Houston in the first round of the NBA playoffs before losing four 
straight to San Antonio. 
</P>
<P>
	The newspaper report, published Thursday, said no contract  
negotiations have begun and that executive vice president Jerry 
West and general manager Mitch Kupchak have yet to formally present 
Rambis as their choice to Lakers owner Jerry Buss. 
</P>
<P>
	``The feeling is this team has to grow together, and you don't  
do that by firing the coach after such a traumatic season,'' one 
source said. 
</P>
<P>
	The newspaper said West and Kupchak surveyed key players about  
Rambis and several -- led by a rousing endorsement from Kobe Bryant 
-- said they would fully support his return. 
</P>
