<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> GM Recalls Some Cadillac Sevilles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- General Motors Corp. is recalling about 35,000  
Cadillac Sevilles from model year 1999 and about 139 from 1998 
because electrical shorts in the generator may cause an engine 
compartment fire. 
</P>
<P>
	Fires have occurred even with the engine off and the key  
removed, GM said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been seven confirmed reports of fires, none of which  
have resulted in injuries, GM said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We want our customers to know that we consider this a serious  
condition,'' said John Smith, Cadillac general manager. ``We have 
started the process of contacting customers so that they can have 
their vehicles serviced as soon as possible at their Cadillac 
dealer.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The recall covers the 1998 vehicles built in August 1998, and  
have vehicle identification numbers greater than WU934376. 
</P>
<P>
	The vehicles should not be parked in an enclosed area, like a  
garage, until they are brought into a dealership, GM said. 

</P>
</TEXT>
