<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Forbes Names Campaign Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Republican presidential candidate Steve Forbes  
has chosen Ohio Secretary of State Ken Blackwell to be national 
chairman of his 2000 presidential campaign. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackwell, one of the party's leading black elected officials,  
will be a top spokesman and strategist for politics and policy, 
Forbes said in an interview with The Associated Press. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's an individual of true principle. He understands the  
principles of my campaign,'' Forbes said. ``Whether the issue is 
taxation or school opportunity, we've been on the same page.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In the joint interview, Blackwell said he believes Forbes is the  
only candidate who can inspire hope, create opportunity and include 
minorities in his political coalition. ``Steve has always been an 
advocate for the politics of inclusion,'' Blackwell said. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackwell, 51, was elected secretary of state in November after  
serving as Ohio's treasurer. He considered running for governor, 
but was persuaded by party leaders to keep the primary clear for 
Bob Taft, who went on to win the governor's race. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackwell was regional chairman of Jack Kemp's 1988 Republican  
presidential campaign and also was county chairman for the 
presidential campaigns of Ronald Reagan and George Bush. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite limited national experience -- he served as an  
undersecretary of Housing and Urban Development and ambassador to 
the U.N. Human Rights Commission in the Bush administration -- 
Blackwell gives Forbes an inroad in Ohio, one of the battleground 
states of the presidential campaign. He also is one of the highest 
ranking minorities in any presidential campaign, Democratic or 
Republican. 
</P>
<P>
	Forbes, who campaigned for Blackwell in 1998, said the new  
chairman was one of the few GOP leaders who fought against a 
proposed sales tax increase in Ohio. ``We've been on the same song 
sheet for a number of years,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackwell is married with three children.  
</P>
</TEXT>
