<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Lower; Dow Down 235.23  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks resumed a downward lurch today as  
continued concerns about interest rates and inflation put the 
brakes on yesterday's rally. The Dow Jones industrial average 
closed down 235.23, a 2.2 percent loss, at 10,466.93. It was the 
ninth-worst point drop ever, and the steepest since Sept. 30, 1998, 
when the blue-chip index fell 237.20. Broader stock indicators were 
all lower, although the Nasdaq composite index, led by slim gains 
from Microsoft and Intel, finished with a relatively slight loss -- 
down 7.98 to 2,419.19. 

</P>
