required it to sell eight stores in Arizona, Wyoming and Utah. But 
it will still have some 3,400 stores from coast to coast. Kroger, 
already the nation's largest grocery, generated $28.2 billion in 
sales last year while Fred Meyer had $14.9 billion. 

</P>
