<HEADLINE> Reverend Gives Prequel Thumbs Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Forget the critics -- the new ``Star Wars'' film  
has earned a glowing review from a leader of the Church of England. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bishop of Oxford, the Right Rev. Richard Harries, said films  
such as ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace'' can reinforce 
``the truth and strength of religion'' because they carry the 
message that goodness will prevail over evil. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think that if people get reassurance that good will overcome  
evil through a film, that far from being a threat to religion, it 
is an echo of what religion, at least the Christian religion, is 
proclaiming,'' Harries told the British Broadcasting Corp. on 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Harries heads one of the Protestant Church of England's 44  
dioceses. 
</P>
